--[[
--   test_01.lua
--   A simple, hand-written map for loading into map mode.
--]]

--[[ NOTES

0) C++ begins counting arrays/vectors from index zero. Lua begins counting tables for index one.

1) When you call "DataManager->Fill*Vector" in C++, it will start with index 1 and count up. If you have an index 0, then that will actually be the *last* item
   filled in the vector! Keep this in mind.

2) However, you can get around #1 by getting the size of the table and then grabbing each element seperately.

3) When using a number to index another table (like in tile_mappings), note that it counts the elements from [0, n-1], even though the indeces of tile_filenames
   actually go from [1, n]. This is because when its loaded into the C++ code, the counting will change (see note #0), and C++ is where the actual indexing is done.

--]]

